	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The French NES uses a custom AV/RF/AC module which converts the composite video from the NES board to RGB output. It has nothing to do with the PPU.
<br />
<br />If you want, you could buy a French NES (if you can find one) and desolder the modules then swap them around.
<br />
<br />
<br />French NES also uses a custom video cable only available in the same places it was. Unless you want to do some creative rewiring, its advisable to get one of those as well.
<br />If you're in PAL territory I'm guessing you'd have SCART. IIRC thats what the FR NES video cable outputs to.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

