<br />
<br />You mean connecting the RGB pins from the SCART to the input of the computer ? If the the signals are compatible between SCART and VGA it would be a good idea.
<br />
<br />Actually, I didnt consider this, because the computer I want to use (the Indy) is hooked up to a LCD screen that uses a proprietary input (not VGA or other usual stuff) where RGB values are transmitted on a digital bus over 24 wires (or is it 48 ?). This is 15y old equipement. At that time there was no standard among LCD screens. The video card is also proprietary and works only with this screen.

		

